Allan Bakke brought a successful http://laws.findlaw.com/us/438/265.html lawsuit against the http://www.universityofcalifornia.edu/regents/ Regents of the University of California in the late 1970s over the special admissions program at the UC Davis School of Medicine. The eventual 54 Supreme Court decision in Bakkes favor is considered a landmark case in the area of wiki:WikiPedia:Affirmative_Action affirmative action. Bakke entered the UC Davis School of Medicine in 1978.

